Last RPM build had fixed MFD_not_spawning bug (for me). But... 

MRR rover started looking like this:

While it was expected to look like this:

Stock "Internal Overlay" is OFF. Though switching it changes nothing.

config is simply 

MODULE
{
    name = JSIAdvTransparentPod
    transparentTransforms = glass
}

Module worked fine with MFD-glitchy RPM build, can't understand why it doesn't now.

Edited April 23, 2016 by Dr. Jet

8 hours ago, dryer_lint said:

Hey guys, I've been trying to install RPM, but it doesn't seem to be working at all. I mean, the capsules are unmodified, and there is no indication that the mod was ever installed.

I installed manually, so that the JSI folder has 4 subfolders.

 

In the log, it shows you have Module Manager 2.6.13.  That is wayyyy outdated (2.6.22 is current).  It also shows a couple of exceptions coming from KerbalEngineer, but your first step is to remove the old MM and install the current one (it is included in the RPM release on GitHub).

 

7 hours ago, Psycho_zs said:

Mk2 inline cockpit needs to be updated. With current RPM it is forced to old IVA which also has wrong POV position.

There has not been an Mk2 inline cockpit in RPM for quite a while now (ever since it was changed for 1.0? 1.04? whenever that was).  You very likely have old MM files due to an overinstall of RPM.  Go look in JSI/RPMPodPatches/PatchesStock for mk1-inline-patch.cfg and mk1-inline-remade-internal.cfg and delete them.  If someone wants to set up a new RPM-enabled IVA for that craft that they're willing to share, I'll be happy to include it.  I don't fly spaceplanes, so it is very unlikely that I will make a new IVA myself.

 

7 hours ago, flatbear said:

are the monitors not working for anyone else in 1.1?

Without additional details, I would guess RPM was installed correctly, or it wasn't updated to the current version, or you're seeing the bug we were discussing on the previous page or two.

Last RPM build had fixed MFD_not_spawning bug (for me). But... 

MRR rover started looking like this:

While it was expected to look like this:

config is simply 

MODULE

    name = JSIAdvTransparentPod
    transparentTransforms = glass

Module worked fine with MFD-glitchy RPM build, can't understand why it doesn't now.

JSIAdvTransparentPod is the new see-through replacement for JSITransparentPod.  It looks like that part was updated to include transparency.  There are still some glitches to sort out with the feature, however.  I think there's a right-click option on the part that can shut it off - if not, you can also delete JSI/JSIAdvTrasparentPods/Plugins/JSIAdvTransparentPods.dll.

JSIAdvTransparentPod is the new see-through replacement for JSITransparentPod.  It looks like that part was updated to include transparency.  There are still some glitches to sort out with the feature, however.  I think there's a right-click option on the part that can shut it off - if not, you can also delete JSI/JSIAdvTrasparentPods/Plugins/JSIAdvTransparentPods.dll.

If I delete or disable it - part will lose transparency where it should be (window).  Actually as close as two days ago it looked fine - just like in 1.0.5 but lacked working MFDs. Now transparency is broken but MFDs are fine.

Edited April 23, 2016 by Dr. Jet

33 minutes ago, Dr. Jet said:

If I delete or disable it - part will lose transparency where it should be (window).  Actually as close as two days ago it looked fine - just like in 1.0.5 but lacked working MFDs. Now transparency is broken but MFDs are fine.

I will have to look into it, and see if @JPLRepo can give me an idea what I may have broken.  The transparency feature has always been a black box for me (Mihara worked on it originally, and JPLRepo worked on the KSP 1.1 version).

EDIT:
 

Oh, yeah - RasterPropMonitor v0.25.1 is out now.  This is essentially identical to the last dev build I posted yesterday, with a tweak to the near plane of external cameras so they can be covered up and have their field of view blocked.  There is a possibility of z-fighting with this change, but my limited testing didn't turn anything up.

Edited April 23, 2016 by MOARdV
RPM v0.25.1

32 minutes ago, JPLRepo said:

You have to follow the instructions for JSIAdvTransparentPods on the WIKI page.
See the very last bullet point.

  1.  What is "DepthShader"? A "DepthMask"? There is nothing except it with syllable "depth" in Unity shaders.
  2.  Already tried to add clone of external mesh to internal mesh. Ended with z-fight.
Edited April 23, 2016 by Dr. Jet

9 minutes ago, Dr. Jet said:
  1.  What is "DepthShader"? A "DepthMask"? There is nothing except it with syllable "depth".
  2.  Already tried to add clone of external mesh to internal mesh. Ended with z-fight.

You have to add a copy of your external mesh to your internal model in unity 5.2.4f1. But make sure you remove cut-outs in this external mesh where you want your windows/transparency to be.
If you have installed PartTools 1.1 there will be a shader called "DepthMask" you must assign this shader to the material on your external mesh copy on the internal model.
Z-fighting should not occur if you change the shader and change the Layer of the external mesh to be Kerbals layer same as the internal mesh.
Take a look at this thread. Also you can load up the stock ones into Blender using the MU importer for stock examples. The stock overlay masks are located in /GameData/Squad/Spaces/OverlayMasks.

Thank you! It looks like it should work. In Unity at least...

Maybe you can clear one more thing for me? How to hide decals (FlagTransform) in part list? When part is selected - they will change to current flag, but in part list they look ugly. Empty texture for KSP/Alpha/Translucent Specular shows white rectangle, using current texture is no good, as making a new fully transparent texture... It must be some shader option which I don't know...
Just wondering, is there a way to rotate cameras in this mod. I can zoom in and out, but not move up/down and left/right.

CKAN has bad metadata for this mod currently: https://github.com/Mihara/RasterPropMonitor/releases/download/v0.25.1.26155/RasterPropMonitor.0.25.1.26155.zip

 

is what it's trying to download, but this URL produces a 404-not-found error.  Going to try to download manually and dump into CKAN's cache dir to unblock, but thought I'd let you know.

27 minutes ago, carranty said:

Just wondering, is there a way to rotate cameras in this mod. I can zoom in and out, but not move up/down and left/right. 

It is possible to configure it, but the "stock" IVA that come with the installation do not have that feature enabled.  If you look at JSI/RPMPodPatches/BasicMFD/MFD40x20.cfg, and you search for "extcamAll", a few lines below that you will see the commented-out buttons for enabling yaw and pitch on the cameras (remove the '//' at the start of those lines to enable those controls).

10 minutes ago, ss8913 said:

CKAN has bad metadata for this mod currently: https://github.com/Mihara/RasterPropMonitor/releases/download/v0.25.1.26155/RasterPropMonitor.0.25.1.26155.zip

 

is what it's trying to download, but this URL produces a 404-not-found error.  Going to try to download manually and dump into CKAN's cache dir to unblock, but thought I'd let you know.

That's an issue for CKAN.  I'm guessing that someone pointed at a hotfix I released earlier, but that release went away after I released a newer hotfix.

Yes, that seems like exactly what happened.  The hotfix number after the version on CKAN is different from the one on your github page.
It would be nice if this mod would be compatible to BD armory.
As a heads-up, there was another "hotfix" release this morning.  It updates JSIAdvTransparentPods to version v0.1.2, but there were no changes to RasterPropMonitor.

https://github.com/Mihara/RasterPropMonitor/pull/512

If KSP-AVC is reporting a version 24.2 of something, it's finding a .version file with that info in it.  You likely have either a full or a partial RPM install squirreled away somewhere else in in GameData.   Perhaps first try searching for all files "*.version" in the GameData directory tree and see what you find.
